text: Did you feel the earthquake?  An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 4.6 was recorded in the North Bay this morning, according to the U.S. Geological Survey.  The quake occurred at 2 : 09 a. m. about 14 miles north - northeast of Healdsburg and had a depth of 1.2 miles.  Did you feel the earthquake?  Have you felt any aftershocks?
